==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cumbrian
<hw>Cum"bri*an</hw> <pr>(k?m"br?-⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to Cumberland, England, or to a system of rocks found
there.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cumbrian system</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>the
slate or graywacke system of rocks, now included in the
<xex>Cambrian</xex> or <xex>Silurian</xex> system; -- so called because
most prominent at Cumberland.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cumbrous</ent>⟦br⟧
